Hello! How can I assist you today with News Break? If you have any questions or need help, feel free to ask!
Where should I put the second Add code to track your conversion event in Create/test web event in the website background?

To track your conversion event using the second ad code, you should place it in the appropriate section of your website's code. If you're using a custom code on your website, ensure it's placed correctly in the `<head>` section of your webpage. If you're using Google Tag Manager (GTM), make sure to create a new tag for the conversion event and test it using GTM's preview mode. For more detailed instructions, you can refer to our [Event Tracking Guidelines](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/14333966189581-How-to-install-a-NewsBreak-Pixel-with-GTM). Let me know if you need further assistance!
Hello, why can't it be detected even though I have added it? It is already transferring. Can you help me check it?
The user has uploaded an image of a webpage containing instructions for tracking a conversion event and testing pixel integration.
Hi there! Could you please clarify what you're trying to detect or transfer? Are you referring to a pixel, postback, or something else? Let me know so I can assist you better!

Thanks for sharing the image! To help you with tracking a conversion event and testing pixel integration, could you let me know which platform you're using? Is it Shopify, GTM, or a custom website? This will help me provide more specific guidance.

Got it! For a custom website, make sure that the base pixel code is correctly placed in the `<head>` section of your webpage. Then, check if the custom event loads after you go through the redirects. If it's a purchase event like `complete_payment`, you'll need to make a test purchase to ensure it triggers correctly. If you're still having issues, verify if the base pixel loads correctly and check if the custom event fires as expected. If you need further assistance, feel free to reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com.
Do you mean I have to try to buy it once on my own website before it can be successful?

Yes, that's correct! To test a purchase event like `complete_payment`, you'll need to simulate a purchase on your own website. This helps ensure that the pixel is firing correctly when the event occurs. If you can't make a purchase, you can reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance.
What does it mean when the ad status shows Warning?

When your ad status shows 'Warning,' it typically means there might be an issue with your ad that needs attention. This could be related to compliance with our ad policies, missing information, or technical issues. I recommend checking the details of the warning message for specific guidance on what needs to be addressed. If you need further help, feel free to contact adsupport@newsbreak.com.
